import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production (Bushels)')
    plt.title('What is the trend in wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    avg_wheat = data.groupby('year')['wheat'].mean()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = avg_wheat.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production per year?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
